The builds start ~5pm EST daily. Commits made before that time will be included in the nightly builds. The build report posts the following day (see time at top of page):

https://www.bioconductor.org/checkResults/release/bioc-LATEST/
https://www.bioconductor.org/checkResults/devel/bioc-LATEST/

If you don't see the package version you expected it's likely you missed the cutoff or didn't push to the git.bioconductor.org server. See git documentation here:

https://www.bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/git/

Valerie


